Drop the insignificant column¶

As we can see the standard deviation of EmployeeCount,StandardHours have SD=0.0,hence we are droping the column also EmployeeNumber & Over18 has no significance impact on dependent variable ,hence droping these columns as well.

Interpretation: As we can see we have High outliers in column - MonthlyIncome, TotalWorkingYears, YearsAtCompany, YearsSinceLastPromotion Moderate outliers in column - YearsSinceLastPromotion Low outliers in column - YearsInCurrentRole, YearsWithCurrManager, NumCompaniesWorked, StockOptionLevel, TrainingTimesLastYear One way to counter this problem is by scaling the variables so as to reduce its effect on the model. The StandardScaler() in Python’s Scikit-learn library can be used for this purpose.

HANDLING CLASS IMBALANCE¶

About 84 % of data are of class label 0 and only 16 % of data are of class label 1.¶
This creates Class Imbalance.¶
It is necessary to remove because even if we create a classifier which everytime predicts Attrition as 'No' will also achieve an overall accuracy of 84%, which is meaningless.¶
In [146]:

#Lets perfrom RepeatedKFold and check the results
from sklearn.model_selection import RepeatedKFold
rkf = RepeatedKFold(n_splits=5, n_repeats=15, random_state=None)
# X is the feature set and y is the target
for train_index, test_index in rkf.split(X,y):
    #print("TRAIN:", train_index, "TEST:", test_index)
    X_train_cv, X_test_cv = X.iloc[train_index], X.iloc[test_index]
    y_train_cv, y_test_cv = y.iloc[train_index], y.iloc[test_index]

Plot the Roc curve¶

Roc is curve is plotted with Tpr on y- axis and Fpr in x-axis.The area under this curve is used as a measure of separability of the model.

In [186]:
# the roc_curve() returns the values for false positive rate, true positive rate and threshold
fpr,tpr,threshold=roc_curve(y_test,y_pred_xgbclassifier)
plt.plot(fpr, tpr)

plt.plot([0, 1], [0, 1],'r--')

plt.title('ROC curve for Attrition Prediction Classifier (Full Model)', fontsize = 12)
plt.xlabel('False positive rate (1-Specificity)', fontsize = 12)
plt.ylabel('True positive rate (Sensitivity)', fontsize = 12)

plt.text(x = 0.02, y = 0.9, s = ('AUC Score:', round(metrics.roc_auc_score(y_test, y_pred_xgbclassifier),4)))
plt.grid(True)

youdens_table = pd.DataFrame({'TPR': tpr,
                             'FPR': fpr,
                             'Threshold': threshold})

# calculate the difference between TPR and FPR for each threshold and store the values in a new column 'Difference'
youdens_table['Difference'] = youdens_table.TPR - youdens_table.FPR

# sort the dataframe based on the values of difference 
# 'ascending = False' sorts the data in descending order
# 'reset_index' resets the index of the dataframe
# 'drop = True' drops the previous index
youdens_table = youdens_table.sort_values('Difference', ascending = False).reset_index(drop = True)

Final Conclusion:¶

As we can see above that XGB classifier has given the highest accuaracy of 93.27 %. To optimise its accuracy more, we have also applied K-fold cross validation & GridSearch CV which basically helped to choose & optimise its hyperparameters and given more refined accuracy of 93.60 %.

Business Conclusions¶

As we can see with feature Importance that feature 'StockOptionLevel' have highest 'Importance' of 0.195269 followed with 'BusinessTravel(0.070595)' & TrainingTimesLastYear'(0.062750) which went almost half in 'Importance' .From this we can conclude that to control'Attrition' we should take care of employees,promote,give timely appraisals and give more materialistic and tangable things .Appreciate and support them more frequently according to there skills and hardwork which will eventually help organisation as well to grow many folds.
